positive.review:
I was really skeptic about this one, but now I wish it was at least x2 longer.

Pros:
- Combat. Once I realised game mechanics I was like "okay, I really like this game now". Sometimes during boss fights it feels like you are NG+ character here. Also don't forget to pick armor based on your enemy attack types;
- Game setting and world overall. Just feels good [spoiler]except for that blood graveyard idk location[/spoiler];
- Game plot. "It is just some dark souls, why should I even bother with checking it?". At some spoilers moment I realised "okay, now I have to replay it and pay attention to the story". And the story is great;
- You CAN and you SHOULD rekt stuff behind walls. This is not elden ring where your enemies can and will attack you thru walls, but you can't. Use it here. Use it a lot;
- Main character. A pleasure for my eyes. Combine it with some armor you can grab...
- Inner demon. I really wish other souls like games would have similar stuff like here. Imagine loosing lots of runes, running back trying to retrive them and then some mf spawns and now you have to deal with it. 10 / 10;
- Skill tree respec. You can safely remove even a single talent and put the point somewhere else. Really good when you wanna change fire damage to poison for example.

Cons:
- Artificial difficulty or idk. It is pretty common to get grabbed by some dude behind totally random corner. But hey, you can rekt stuff thru textures so simply bonk random wall if you feel sus - there 90% will be some spearman;
- Monster type bosses. Almost all of them feels like have elden ring moment hit boxes;
- NG+ balance. At least at my first NG+ feels like I could spew at my enemies and they just die. The game gets balanced a bit later tho.

Worth the price. I didn't get bored even after multiple NG games. Wish you guys GL at making another even better game.
